-- Peru Stocks: Atacocha, Candente, Minsur, Rio Cristal, Southern
-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 2012-01-30T21:20:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-30/peru-stocks-atacocha-candente-minsur-rio-cristal-southern.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4:10 p.m. local time.  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  was little changed at 21,852.10. The
 MSCI All Peru Capped Index (MXPECAPD)  slid 0.5 percent to 2,789.27.  Copper, zinc and tin miners slumped after U.S. stocks fell
and metals declined in  New York  and  London , said Inteligo SAB
analyst Rodrigo Zuazo.  Rio Cristal Resources Corp. (RCZ)  , a Canadian
exploration company, fell 7.1 percent to 13 cents.  Southern
Copper Corp. (PCU\C)  (SCCO PE), Peru’s biggest copper producer, dropped
3.9 percent to $34.68. The company is expected to publish
fourth-quarter earnings this week.  Cia. Minera Atacocha SA (CMA\B) 
(ATACOBC1 PE), the Lima-based zinc mining company, declined for
the third session in four, losing 2.4 percent to 81 centimos.
 Minsur SA (MINSURI1)  (MINSURI1 PE), the world’s fourth-largest tin
producer, slid 2.3 percent to 2.96 soles.  Candente Copper Corp. (DNT) 
, a Canadian mining exploration company with operations
in Peru, fell 1.9 percent to $1.02.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alex Emery  in  Lima  at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  